#. [scenario]: id=10_Tears_in_Hell
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:3
msgid "Tears in Hell"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:10
msgid ""
"With Luxor dead, Jacques and Kyoko eyed the Book of Prophecies with "
"distrust. How strong could the power of the written word be?"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:13
msgid ""
"Jacques gathered up the courage and opened the book. As he looked at a "
"random page, suddenly the Book absorbed him, pulled him inside. His head was "
"filled with images, for that is how the book truly communicated with its "
"reader. Jacques realised the images were of Mosh, just as he had dreamt of "
"it a few nights earlier."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:16
msgid ""
"This time, however, he could see himself as if he was someone else, and he "
"was indeed a terrifying sight. He was storming through the crowds, raving "
"with madness, hacking left and right, drenched in the blood of those who "
"happened to be in his way. He was slowly making his way to what appeared to "
"be a tomb. As his raving self approached it, he realised that there was "
"something written on it. It was just one word - 'Jacques'."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:19
msgid ""
"Jacques cried and was thrown away from the book. He was drenched in sweat as "
"Kyoko leaned over him in concern. He would not tell her what he saw, and, in "
"shock, could not stop her as she lifted the Book up herself."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:22
msgid ""
"As she was swept in the universe of the Book, Kyoko saw a small underground "
"cavern, falling apart and being swollen by lava. It was a sad sight, "
"depressingly filled with bones of its inhabitants. It was not a familiar "
"sight, and yet it somehow seemed familiar. As she strained her memory, she "
"finally recognised it: it was her father's court, only disfigured almost "
"beyond recognition."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:25
msgid ""
"With a snap, Kyoko closed the Book. Ruphulus and his minions must have "
"attacked. Father was in danger! She shook Jacques and yelled at him to make "
"haste. They had to go back, and go back fast, if it was not already too "
"late..."
msgstr ""

#. [side]: id=Jacques, type=Battle_Commander
#. [event]
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:39
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:93
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/12_Flip_of_Destiny.cfg:36
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/12_Flip_of_Destiny.cfg:76
msgid "Jacques"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kyoko
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:100
msgid "Father! Oh no! How could this happen?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:104
msgid ""
"The chamber is very different indeed. Jacques thinks back to when he first "
"saw it and can not believe how much it has changed. Gone are the pools of "
"water and the plants, gone are the nice decorations. Now, the chamber is "
"barren, the pools are of lava and the decorations are the skulls of the "
"defeated warriors."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Jacques
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:109
msgid "Kyoko, I'm sorry. I know how you must..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kyoko
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:113
msgid ""
"No! I shouldn't have gone to the Shadowlands, and I shouldn't find hope in a "
"dashing young stranger, thinking he would be capable of defeating such a "
"deadly foe. I was a fool..."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: speaker=narrator
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:117
msgid ""
"Kyoko falls to the ground and weeps for her father and her people, as three "
"figures suddenly rush out into the chamber."
msgstr ""

#. [unit]: type=Dwarvish Runemaster, id=King Bombasan
#. [side]: type=Dwarvish Runemaster, id=King Bombasan
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:130
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/2_Captivity.cfg:110
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/7_Confronting_the_Traitor.cfg:51
msgid "King Bombasan"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Bombasan
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:161
msgid ""
"We thought we heard a human voice coming from here! My dear daughter, it is "
"so good to see you back alive and well!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kyoko
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:165
msgid "Father! You're alive!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Bombasan
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:169
msgid ""
"Of course I am, child. These old bones will not be rattled so easily. But "
"the fighting is hard, and you came back in the nick of time."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Jacques
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:173
msgid ""
"How come the chamber is so ravaged? It would appear as if Ruphulus had "
"already had its way with it."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Bombasan
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:177
msgid ""
"And so he did. They launched a surprise attack on us soon after you left. "
"The walls behind the chamber suddenly collapsed and they stormed in from a "
"passage they had built from their infernal domains. They took many of us "
"that day and the rest escaped down several tunnels."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Bombasan
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:181
msgid ""
"It took us days to regroup, until we could finally launch a counter-attack "
"and push them back. We were quite succesful at first, but our numbers keep "
"dwindling while theirs seem inexhaustible."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kyoko
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:185
msgid ""
"But who are they? Who do you speak of, father, that is the army of Ruphulus?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Bombasan
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:189
msgid ""
"You may almost wish you did not ask, for it is an army of the dead. Often "
"times, all you see are the bones of the people that once lived but are no "
"more. I now see what Ruphulus' plan was in having us fight the beasts on the "
"desert plains outside. The fallen provided him with the supply of the "
"unfortunate materials for his ghastly army."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Jacques
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:193
msgid ""
"Actually, it appears he also had an agreement with the Shadowhounds, who "
"were shipping the remains of their own fallen victims. And from these "
"remains he had suddenly constructed an army? What evil magic is this?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Bombasan
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:197
msgid ""
"The worst kind, I suppose. But let us not tarry, for the battle is getting "
"worse by the minute. Do you have any good news, perhaps? Is help on its way?"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Jacques
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:201
msgid ""
"We have the Book, although it is unclear how it will help us defeat "
"Ruphulus. More importantly, we have enough seasoned warriors with us to make "
"the undead of Ruphulus reconsider their decision to continue rattling their "
"bones!"
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=Kyoko
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:205
msgid ""
"I will consult the Book of Prophecies, and hopefully it will become clearer "
"what needs to be done."
msgstr ""

#. [message]: id=King Bombasan
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/10_Tears_in_Hell.cfg:209
msgid ""
"Good! Aye, there is hope, still! Let us run, now, and descend to the lower "
"depths of this abyss, where we have set up camp to defend against the next "
"onslaught of the undead beasts. There, we can plan our next move and then "
"try to drive this menace out of our lands!"
msgstr ""

#. [scenario]: id=11_The_Day_of_Reckoning
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/11_The_Day_of_Reckoning.cfg:3
msgid "The Day of Reckoning"
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/11_The_Day_of_Reckoning.cfg:10
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/11_The_Day_of_Reckoning.cfg:22
msgid "This was it."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/11_The_Day_of_Reckoning.cfg:13
msgid ""
"Jacques followed the King and the remaining soldiers ever deeper down the "
"cave, until they came to a makeshift encampment at the edge of a wide "
"corridor. Jacques wondered what waited for them at the other side. At the "
"very end, there would be Ruphulus, but Jacques didn't even want to imagine "
"how many bones they would have to crack to get to him."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/11_The_Day_of_Reckoning.cfg:16
msgid ""
"Along the way, the King and Kyoko were deep in conversation, with the King "
"stealing a glance now and then towards the book that Kyoko grasped firmly in "
"her hands. Curious though he was, he knew the book was not his riddle to "
"solve, as he was not the one who first heard its call."
msgstr ""

#. [part]
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/11_The_Day_of_Reckoning.cfg:19
msgid ""
"As they reached the encampment, Jacques immediately set off to examine the "
"troops and boost their confidence. This was the time they both dreaded and "
"hoped for - the time of reckoning, when they could settle the score with "
"their evil adversary and truly break his chains."
msgstr ""

#. [side]: id=Jacques, type=Thief
#. [event]
#. [side]: id=Jacques, type=Battle_Commander
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg:41
#: A_Rough_Life/scenarios/8_The_Shadowlands.cfg:142
